  <titles>
    <title type="display">Medical Debt Relief Act of 2020</title>
    <title type="short" as="introduced">Medical Debt Relief Act of 2020</title>
    <title type="official" as="introduced">To amend the Fair Credit Reporting Act to institute a 1-year waiting period before medical debt will be reported on a consumer's credit report and to remove paid-off and settled medical debts from credit reports that have been fully paid or settled, to amend the Fair Debt Collection Practices Act to provide a timetable for verification of medical debt and to increase the efficiency of credit markets with more perfect information, and for other purposes.</title>
